But the subject of our Pen,Of the three Eclipses 1652 is onely three Eclipses of this Year 1652. Viz. two of the Moone and one of the Sunne, a very Memorable one; at which I beleeve Ambrose Merlin hinted, when in one of his Brittish Prophesies, mentioning the year 1652. he cals it A Darke Yeare;

                  Merlin cals 1652. a darke year. which he might very well do, in regard the first Eclips of the Moone, the fifteenth of March, there will be almost ten digits Eclipsed; two digits more had made a totall obscuration; and in that of the Sunne the twenty ninth day of March, there will be eleven digits and fifty five minutes Eclipsed as Captain George Wharton hath acurately and learnedly delivers in his Hemeroscopeion.
               Captain Wharton an excellent Calculator.

These things, and such actions are wholly of the nature of the fiery Trigon: Praedominium elementi ignei, ad Reges Civitatumque praefectos, rerum quoque publicarum maximos motus designari;

                  Cornelius Gemma, of the fiery Trigon, or fiery Element
               praecipuè vero seditiones populi, quanquam & mutationes legum magna ex parte subsequuntur. The Praedominion of the fiery Element having influence over men, doth design accidents to ensue unto Kings, Rulers of Commonwealths and Cities; especiall relation it hath in manifesting the seditions or uproars of people; yet ever these things are accompanied with the change of Customes, Lawes, and Ceremonies in Religion, with Schisms, Heresies, &c. all prodigies end in Schisms.
